The Bank of England said it provided themarket with a further 68 mln stg assistance this afternoon,bringing its total assistance on the day to 143 mln stg.   Shortly before, the Bank said it had revised its estimateof the shortage up to 450 mln stg from the earlier forecast of400 mln.    During the afternoon, the bank bought 22 mln stg of bandtwo bank bills at 9-13/16 pct and two mln stg of localauthority bills plus 44 mln stg of bank bills in band four at9-11/16 pct. These rates were in all cases unchanged fromprevious intervention levels. REUTER&#3;